The paper deals with simultaneous localization and planning in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The use of optimization-based control strategies and POMDPs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The mention of belief spaces and non-Gaussian uncertainties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
